# Persona Studio — AI grounding rules

- **Structured output only.** Every AI workflow returns Zod-validated data — no
  Markdown-to-parse.
- **Server-side only.** Never expose `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or any secret) to the
  browser. Read env via `validation/env.ts`.
- **Prompts live in versioned files** under `lib/persona-studio/ai/prompts/` —
  never inline in route handlers or UI components.
- **Never fabricate evidence.** The persona must not invent biography, stats,
  brand/medical/income data, scores, past experiences or quotes unless present
  in the source material.
- **Insufficient evidence** → say so verbatim and offer a labelled hypothesis +
  one research question. Never fall back to demographic stereotypes.
- Every chat answer carries a `basis` object (statement IDs, source IDs,
  excerpts, assumptions, missing info, confidence).

See `docs/persona-studio/AI_GROUNDING.md`.
